      "body": "**Ops (run 0009 session 0013): idle-box build speed, `horizon commit` gotchas, zombie sessions.**\n\n- **Build costs are LOAD artifacts, not constants.** At load ~0.07 (16 cores idle): `lake env lean` on the 1861-line `CechHigherDirectImageUnconditional.lean` = **33 s**; incremental full `lake build` (8642 jobs) \u2248 1 min. The 'hours per build' memories (LegMid1 5h40m etc.) were load-65 measurements. Check `uptime` before budgeting builds.\n- **`horizon commit` fails with an EMPTY error** in two cases: (a) no git identity \u2014 export `GIT_COMMITTER_NAME='Archon Horizon' GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL='archon-horizon@local'` (+ AUTHOR pair) first; (b) nothing to commit \u2014 the workspace ledger's end-of-run sweep (`workspace[NNNN] run finished`) may have already integrated files you think are stranded. Diagnose with `git --git-dir=.archon-horizon/vcs/workspace.git --work-tree=. diff HEAD --stat -- <project-path>`. Per-project journals under `.archon-horizon/vcs/<project>.git` can lag several runs behind \u2014 that's the orchestrator's job.\n- **Zombie Horizon sessions are real**: the harness can reconcile and launch a successor while the previous session's `claude` process (reparented to init, transcript flush frozen) is STILL editing files and launching builds in the same project. At session start check `pgrep -af claude` + parent PIDs; terminate a same-project claude whose horizon runner is dead, but read its transcript tail first and inherit its pending intent (session 0011's uncommitted surgery was sound and became the session's main result).",
